I had the same issue on TF 1.4 with the speech_commands example. It turns out that I had absentmindedly removed this from the top of label_wav.py, thinking that it was unused:

# pylint: disable=unused-import
from tensorflow.contrib.framework.python.ops import audio_ops as contrib_audio
# pylint: enable=unused-import

It turns out having contrib_audio.decode_wav in scope is essential to loading the graph.

I realize this isn't exactly the same as the original issue, but perhaps others who are modifying label_wav.py or writing a custom loader will, as I did, find this through google.

body:
I had the same issue on TF 1.4 with the speech_commands example. It turns out that I had absentmindedly removed this from the top of `label_wav.py`, thinking that it was unused:

```
# pylint: disable=unused-import
from tensorflow.contrib.framework.python.ops import audio_ops as contrib_audio
# pylint: enable=unused-import
```

It turns out having `contrib_audio.decode_wav` in scope is essential to loading the graph.

I realize this isn't exactly the same as the original issue, but perhaps others who are modifying `label_wav.py` or writing a custom loader will, as I did, find this through google.
